# Design iteration workflow

Before changing the design or content of this site:

1. Read `SITE_INFO.md` (source of truth for links, email, copy) and
   `AI_DESIGN_LOG.md` (past changes + known gotchas).
2. After making changes, append a dated entry to `AI_DESIGN_LOG.md` describing
   what changed and any new pitfalls — so future iterations don't repeat them.
   Keep it lean.

# `index.html` is a self-extracting bundle, not plain HTML

- Visible content lives as a JSON-encoded HTML string inside
  `<script type="__bundler/template">`; assets are gzip+base64 in
  `<script type="__bundler/manifest">`. Don't search/replace raw markup.
- When rewriting the template, `JSON.stringify` does NOT escape `/`. Re-escape
  `</script` -> `<\u002Fscript`, or the page breaks.
- After editing, verify both template and manifest still `JSON.parse` cleanly.
- Keep asset paths relative (served from the `/scalentic-homepage/` subpath).
- For anything beyond tiny link/text tweaks, regenerate the page fresh from
  `SITE_INFO.md` rather than hand-editing the bundle.
